-1339679579.text: "By contrast, when transducted with AdPTENWT, the phosphorylation levels of PDK1 (ser 241), AKT (Ser 473 and Thr 308), and ERK1/2 were significantly reduced to 0.38-fold (P < 0.05), 0.21-fold (P < 0.05), 0.28-fold (P < 0.05), and 0.61-fold (P < 0.05) of the control, respectively, suggesting that overexpression of PTEN modulates the basal activities of both PI3K-AKT and MAPK-ERK cascades."
